  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed first floor side extension by reason of its width and insufficient setback from the common shared boundary with Number 43&amp;nbsp;Westrow Drive&amp;nbsp;would be an incongruous and unsympathetic addition that would contribute to terracing effect by closing the gap and losing the openness between terrace groups. The development would cause harm to the character and appearance of the host dwelling and wider surrounding street scene and it would be contrary to:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paragraphs 131 and 135 of the National Planning Policy Framework (December 2023)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policy D4 of the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policy CP3&amp;nbsp;of the Core Strategy (July 2010)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policy BP11&amp;nbsp;of the Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Policies SP 2, DMD 1, and DMD 6 of the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s&amp;nbsp;draft&amp;nbsp;Local Plan 2037 (December 2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paragraph 5.4.2(a) of the&amp;nbsp;Council&#x27;s&amp;nbsp;Residential Extensions and Alterations&amp;nbsp;Supplementary Planning Documents&amp;nbsp;(February 2012)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The internal use of the proposed first floor side extension would be a single person bedroom. The proposed bedroom would fail to comply with&amp;nbsp;the minimum national internal space standards and it would&amp;nbsp;be contrary&amp;nbsp;to:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paragraph 10(c) in the Technical housing standards – nationally\r\ndescribed space standard (March 2015)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Part F(3) in Policy D6 of the London Plan (March 2021)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;"
  ],
